race.comment: Very tough - not many of these do much winning. HANAFUBUKI (3) is racing well but just cannot find the post first, often short in betting. She's been beaten at $2.15 and $3.10 her past two but this does look incredibly winnable. HOLLANDIA (5) is similarly racing well, sticking on fairly here last week. On the quick turnaround here could suit. REBADGE (6) hasn't been far away his past couple and should take holding out. HOLLY'S STAR (12) Did her best work late last time over 2540m at Cranbourne, finishing second. Well placed to feature. WINTER GRACE (11) has looked good in her 10 career starts, most recently scoring by half a length over 1950m at Yarra Valley. This is tougher but can make an impact.
